        <h1 class="page-heading"> CodeCrafters Hub Documentation </h1>

        <h3 class="page-subheading-1">Introduction</h3>

        <p class="introduction-p">
            Welcome to CodeCrafters Hub, an engaging and interactive blog website dedicated to providing insightful
            articles, tutorials, and resources for developers at all levels.<br> Our mission is to foster a community
            where
            developers can learn, share, and grow together. <br> This documentation provides an overview of the
            website's
            structure, features, and guidelines to help you navigate and contribute to CodeCrafters Hub effectively.
        </p>

        <h3 class="page-subheading-2">Website Structure</h3>

        <div class="home-page-section">
            <h5 class="page-minisubheading-1">Home Page</h5>
            <p class="home-page-descriptions">
                The home page serves as the entry point to CodeCrafters Hub.
                <br>
                Navigation Bar: Links to different sections of the website, including Home, Blog, About, and Contact.
                <br>
                Featured Articles: A showcase of the most popular and recent articles.
                <br>
                Search Bar: Allows users to search for articles and content within the site.
            </p>

        </div>

        <div class="blog-section">

            <h5 class="page-minisubheading-2">Blog Section</h5>
            <p class="blog-section-description">
                The Blog section is the heart of CodeCrafters Hub.
                <br>
                Article Listings: A list of all published articles, displayed with titles, summaries, and publication
                dates.
                <br>Categories: Articles are categorized for easy navigation (e.g., Front-End Development, Back-End
                Development, Tutorials, Tips & Tricks).
                <br>Tags: Tags help users find articles on specific topics (e.g., JavaScript, Node.js, CSS).
            </p>

        </div>

        <div class="about-page">

            <h5 class="page-minisubheading-3">About Page</h5>
            <p class="about-page-description">
                The About page provides information about CodeCrafters Hub, its mission, and the team behind it.
                <br>
                Mission Statement: An overview of the goals and values of CodeCrafters Hub. <br>
                Team Information: Profiles of the contributors and team members.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Page Section 2-->
    <div class="section-2">
        <h3 class="page-subheading-3">Features</h3>

        <h5 class="page-minisubheading-4"> EJS Templating</h5>
        <p class="ejs-templating-paragraph">
            CodeCrafters Hub uses EJS (Embedded JavaScript) templating to dynamically render content on the website.<br>
            This allows for the inclusion of JavaScript code within HTML templates, enabling a seamless and interactive
            user experience.
        </p>

        <h5 class="page-minisubheading-5"> Bootstrap Integration </h5>
        <p class="bootstrap-integration-paragraph">
            The website is styled using Bootstrap, a popular CSS framework. <br>Bootstrap provides a responsive and visually
            appealing design, <br>ensuring that the website looks great on all devices, from desktops to mobile phones.
        </p>


        <h5 class="page-minisubheading-6">CSS Flexbox</h5>

        <p class="css-flexbox-paragraph">
            CSS Flexbox is used to create flexible and responsive layouts.<br> It allows for the arrangement of content in a
            way that adapts to <br>different screen sizes and orientations, enhancing the overall user experience.
        </p>


        <h5 class="page-minisubheading-7">Commenting System</h5>
        <p class="commenting-system-paragraph">
            The commenting system enables users to interact with articles by leaving comments. <br> This feature promotes
            engagement and community building among readers and authors.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Page Section 3-->
    <div class="section-3">
        <h3 class="page-subheading-4">Contribution Guidelines</h3>

        <h5 class="page-minisubheading-8">Writing Articles</h5>
        <p class="writing-articles-paragraph">

            To contribute an article to CodeCrafters Hub: <br>

            Create an Account: Sign up for an account on the website. <br>
            Submit an Article: Use the "Submit Article" feature to upload your article.<br>
            Review Process: Articles are reviewed by the editorial team before publication. <br>
            Publication: Once approved, your article will be published and featured on the website
        </p>



        <h5 class="page-minisubheading-9">Commenting</h5>
        <p class="commenting-paragraph">
            Users are encouraged to leave comments on articles to share their thoughts and engage in discussions. <br>Please
            adhere to the following guidelines: <br>

            Respectful Communication: Be respectful and considerate in your comments. <br>
            Constructive Feedback: Provide constructive feedback and avoid negativity. <br>
            Stay On Topic: Keep comments relevant to the article being discussed.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Page Section 4-->
    <div class="section-4">
